Welcome to the administrators' noticeboard








This page is for posting information and issues that affect administrators.

Sections older than six days are
archived by Lowercase sigmabot III.




Issues appropriate for this page include general announcements, discussion of administration methods, ban proposals, block reviews, and backlog notices.
If you are seeking administrator intervention for a specific issue or dispute, you should post it at the Administrators' noticeboard for incidents (ANI) instead.
Do not report issues requiring oversight to this page â€“ email oversight-en-wpwikimedia.org directly with your concern.




Click here to purge this page
(For help, see Wikipedia:Purge)




Shortcuts:

WP:AN
WP:ANB







When you start a discussion about an editor, you must leave a notice on the editor's talk page.
The use of ping or the notification system is not sufficient for this purpose.
You may use {{subst:AN-notice}} ~~~~ to do so.











Â 
Are you in the right place?









Permanent deletion of sensitive personal information â†’ requests for oversight. Please DO NOT make such requests here; reports here are visible to everyone.
Vandalism or spamming â†’ administrator intervention against vandalism.
Impolite or uncivil communications â†’ consider the advice at the civility policy page.
Page protection â†’ requests for page protection.
Edit warring â†’ the administrators' edit warring noticeboard.
Suspected sockpuppetry â†’ sockpuppet investigations.
Improper usernames â†’ usernames for administrator attention.
Administrative backlogs â†’ you can add {{Admin backlog}} to the backlogged page or post a notice here.
Cut and paste moves/history merge â†’ requests for history merge.
Review of the deletion or undeletion of a page â†’ deletion review.
Review of the close or requested move discussion of a page â†’ Move review.
Assistance in resolving disputes â†’ dispute resolution.
Issues not requiring administrative tools (content concerns, naming conventions...) â†’ the Village Pump or Editor assistance requests.
Evasion of blocks, abuse of admin tools, or other incidents â†’ Wikipedia:Administrators' noticeboard/Incidents (WP:ANI)
If you are blocked â†’ place the code: {{Unblock|Your reason for unblock}}Â â€“ on your talk page. You may also contact the blocking admin via email (navigate to their userpage and click "Email this user"). If you can't edit your talk page, you may appeal your block via Wikipedia:Unblock Ticket Request System.
Issues regarding Wikimedia projects other than the English Wikipedia â†’ Meta-Wiki.










